parameter 5: In the original airing, 'Martin Lawrence (I)' (qv) performed a monologue featuring jokes about feminine hygiene (as performed in _You So Crazy (1994)_ (qv)). In all subsequent reruns, after the start of this particular bit, the screen fades to black and a voiceover reads the following announcement: "At this point in his monologue, Martin begins a commentary on what he considers the decline in standards of feminine hygiene in this country. Although we at Saturday Night Live take no stand on this issue one way or the other, network policy prevents us from re-broadcasting this portion of his remarks. In summary, Martin feels, or felt at the time, that the failure of many young women to bathe thoroughly is a serious problem that demands our attention. He explores this problem, citing numerous examples from his personal experience, and ends by proposing several imaginative solutions. It was a frank and lively presentation, and nearly cost us all our jobs. We now return to the conclusion of Martin's monologue."
